         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <choice corresp="#a1">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">“... but you know.” He would fear him: “You ...” [114a]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a2">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">[114b] (The good Law?) has been approved beginning with the Sūtra belonging to the omniscient, the teacher. [114c]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">114. In the Udānālaṅkāra (the second part) of the Cittavarga (is finished).</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... erroneous (doctrines?) belonging (to heretics?), [1a] and this one is not able to receive the good Law.</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a5">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [1b] ... he [1c] has got a large depression [and] he does not shine in his</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a6">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">company. 1. ... The Buddha (was staying) ... together with five hundred pupils.</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a7">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... and (someone) told that to the omniscient. 2. ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b1">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (the ones) related to the saying in ... manner. [3b] The [alternative] sides ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b2">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he will make the om sound. 3. They began to utter (noise) ... [4a]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [4b] And they could not stay on the (virtuous) side. [4c] They did (not) understand ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (4). The monks heard that matter. [5a] Together with a heretic ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b5">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Thereupon) they let this matter be known to (the Buddha lord). [5c] Following that (the Buddha lord spoke this stanza: 5)</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b6">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">“(By the one who is not stable in his mind), [by the one] not knowing [6a] the good Law, [= Uv 31.28a-b], [by the one] (whose) faith [is] wavering, [6b] (the wisdom is not fulfilled.) [6c] [= Uv 31.28c-d]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b7">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">And (now) in this stanza I will (explain) the matter in detail.” 6.</seg></seg>
               </choice>
            </p>
